00:00:00,059 --> 00:00:04,029
Pull over where it's safe to do so, apply the hand brake

6
00:00:04,029 --> 00:00:08,930
and put the vehicle into first gear. Grab
your vehicle jacking equipment from 

7
00:00:08,930 --> 00:00:12,699
under the mats in the boot and jack up the car
slightly from under the jacking points.

8
00:00:12,699 --> 00:00:18,540
If you have any wheel chocks place them
under the opposite wheel

9
00:00:18,540 --> 00:00:25,540
from the wheel affected.

10
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:28,850
If you have a locking wheel nut, be sure
to have this in hand.

11
00:00:28,850 --> 00:00:32,480
place the locking wheel nut on the locking wheel nut

12
00:00:32,480 --> 00:00:36,160
bolt.

13
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:39,750
Should you be using the wrench, be sure to
select the right direction.

14
00:00:39,750 --> 00:00:43,750
Consult your vehicle manual to correct
all settings

15
00:00:43,750 --> 00:00:47,460
if you're using the torque wrench. Remove each bolt

16
00:00:47,460 --> 00:00:54,460
and keep safe nearby.

17
00:00:58,880 --> 00:01:05,880
Jack up the car slightly higher to free
the wheel. Remove the wheel.

